After completed oauth, there is currently no way to undo it.
User should be able to click on the "locked" icon to change it to "unlocked" icon.
It's very inconvenient for us to do testing. Currently I have to delete the gadget and then add it back.

If you have the query

{code}
issue inwatchedIssues()
{code}

the autocomplete parser thinks this is cool and it is not.

The string based operators should require a space between them and the value.

Paste the following query into the text area:

{quote}
(not (resolutiondate <= "2008-01-01") and (type in (Improvement)) or "Priority for beta phase" = 3) and
assignee = currentUser() order by status
{quote}

No more suggestions on the second line, and query parse indicator broken

Only in Firefox 3.x if you create this query:

{code}
reporter in (fschmitz, bbain, "dylan@atlassian.com", mtokar) and status = "Content Modification Needed" AND component in (JQL) ORDER BY created
{code}

Then if you try to replace the status it will replace it all the way to the end of the query, this does not happen in Safari or IE8.

If you create a query like

{code}
filter = ADV_Q2_07  AND summary ~ foo
{code}

If you try to edit this and place your cursor at the AND it will suggest ORDER BY even though this would make your query invalid.

Not sure if we care to fix this, it is probably not worth it.
